                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጊዮርጊስ፡</foreign>
                      </seg>
                        <desc>The words Mary, Jesus Christ, and George are rubricated</desc>
                        <desc>Occasionally, the name Jesus Christ is written in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#20v #21r" facs="024">fols. 20v, 21r</locus>)</desc>
